reviewText: I liked the plotline. Excellent finish. While the actors did the best with what skills they possessed, this storyline might have benefitted from a more seasoned cast that could have taken this to at least 90 minutes.

I really thought it was going to go more indepth about how awful Hell is.  It was a good clip for what it was.  But I was expecting more.  I needed a hair raising movie.  One that would scare Hell out of you.

Too short and not the best acting but it will do.

this movie was a good evangelistic show. its good but the only thing i didn't know was how he passed away. also, i understand it was a little nice as not to frighten teens too much, but i was looking for a more realistic show. other than that, its ok. worth buying too. :)
